  "body":"First pass at Dark Mode color scheme. Updates all components except Buttons (waiting on #237) with a couple new colors. Dark Mode background is tones of flat grey, and the link/highlight/etc. colors are muted versions of their Light Mode form.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1944\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2020-07-12 at 1 43 19 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/98312/87253013-a815a600-c445-11ea-976e-a7fba0a533e2.png\">\r\n\r\n**New Colors**\r\n- `border-color` Whenever you're making a divider line, 1px shadow, or border, strongly consider the Border color\r\n- `background-color` Replaces `app-bg-color` and fulfills the same purpose\r\n- `background-minus-1`, `background-minus-2`, for elevations _below_ the app's primary background surface. Currently used for the right sidebar.\r\n- `background-plus-1`, `background-plus-2`, for elevations _above_ the app's primary background surface. Currently used for dropdown and Athena.\r\n\r\n**Help Wanted**\r\n- The darker colors are currently just replacing the light mode colors. These color sets should be collected into themes and users should be able to switch between them.",
